{"declarations":[{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Mathlib/Data/Seq/Defs.html#Stream'.Seq.Pairwise\"><span class=\"name\">Stream'</span>.<span class=\"name\">Seq</span>.<span class=\"name\">Pairwise</span></a></span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">α</span> : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> u}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">R</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">α</span> → <span class=\"fn\">α</span> → <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Prop</a></span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">s</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Data/Seq/Defs.html#Stream'.Seq\">Seq</a> <span class=\"fn\">α</span></span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Prop</a></div></div>","info":{"doc":"`Pairwise R s` means that all the elements with earlier indices are\n`R`-related to all the elements with later indices.\n```\nPairwise R [1, 2, 3] ↔ R 1 2 ∧ R 1 3 ∧ R 2 3\n```\nFor example if `R = (· ≠ ·)` then it asserts `s` has no duplicates,\nand if `R = (· < ·)` then it asserts that `s` is (strictly) sorted.\n","docLink":"./Mathlib/Data/Seq/Defs.html#Stream'.Seq.Pairwise","kind":"def","line":759,"name":"Stream'.Seq.Pairwise","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/0f1dd7505c3d08b5feb82300ccc73179a457bf51/Mathlib/Data/Seq/Defs.lean#L759-L769"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Mathlib/Data/Seq/Defs.html#Stream'.Seq.set\"><span class=\"name\">Stream'</span>.<span class=\"name\">Seq</span>.<span class=\"name\">set</span></a></span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span c